urns service users into 'consumers' of services within a care market and hence reinforces the commodification of care which sees vast profits made by a small number of providers at the expense of good quality services for those who use them.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh1 aBeresford, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeresford, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarr, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerguson, Iain, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLavalette, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMain, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPile, Helga, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoulstone, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlasberg, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSlorach, Roddy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStack, Pat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z978311119621340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447366799423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447366799/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles